            <article class="layout-article" id="firehose-45580737">
        <header class="story-header">
            
            <h1 id="title-45580737"><a href="//news-beta.slashdot.org/story/13/04/18/2215200/kobo-ceo-says-not-selling-washing-machines-key-to-overtaking-amazon">Kobo CEO Says Not Selling Washing Machines Key To Overtaking Amazon</a></h1>
            
                <h4>
                    
                    <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/~samzenpus" class="author">samzenpus</a> posted  about a year ago  | from the we-do-one-thing-we-do-it-very-well-and-then-we-move-on dept. 
                    

                    
                </h4>
            
                <span class="topic" id="topic-45580737"> <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/index2.pl?fhfilter=books" onclick="return addfhfilter('books');">
            <img src="//c.fsdn.com/s/topics/books_64.png" width="30px" height="30px" alt="Books" title="Books">
        </a></span>
                <a href="//news-beta.slashdot.org/story/13/04/18/2215200/kobo-ceo-says-not-selling-washing-machines-key-to-overtaking-amazon"><span class="comment-count">207</span></a>
        </header>
	
            
        <div class="elips" data-link="//news-beta.slashdot.org/story/13/04/18/2215200/kobo-ceo-says-not-selling-washing-machines-key-to-overtaking-amazon">
            <p  id="text-45580737">
                    
                        DavidGilbert99 writes <i>"Kobo, the Canadian-based ebook company is number two in the market, behind the behemoth that is Amazon. So what does the CEO Michael Serbinis think is the one thing which will <a href="http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/articles/458590/20130418/kobo-focus-readers-first-battle-amazon.htm">allow them to overtake the e-commerce giant</a>? 'We don't sell any washing machines, we don't sell radios. We are not focused on the next server farm to offer data services. It is a question of focus.' Serbinis goes on to tell IBTimes UK: 'From an organization standpoint at Kobo, this is all we do. Everyone at Kobo, all we focus on is creating a great experience for book-lovers.'"</i>
                        
                    
            </p>
        </div>
        <footer class="article-footer">
            
        </footer>
	
    </article>
