        <header data-points="1" data-reason="Insightful">
            <h3 class="comment-title" data-subject="No Android App"><i class="com-toggle fa fa-caret-down"></i>No Android App<span> (1, Insightful)</span></h3>
            <h4 class="avatar-tiny"><a href="//beta.slashdot.org/~swillden" class="author" title="author name and user ID">swillden (191260) </a> | about a year ago | <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=3663727&cid=43488005">(#43488005)</a></h4>
        </header>
        <div id="comment_body_43488005" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="1" data-reason="Insightful">
            <div class="comment-body">I won't even seriously consider them until I can read their books on my tablet and phone. I was an early adopter of eBooks, buying my first Rocket eBook reader back around 1998, so I don't have anything against dedicated devices, but there's no longer any need, and I already carry a phone and a tablet which both work great as eBook readers... and with all three of the eBook reader apps I use I can even bounce back and forth between devices, reading on my tablet when it's handy or on my phone when the tablet isn't nearby.</div>
